{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856787692,"sessionID":"ses_286b0173effehMzZXYWbZMW44j","part":{"id":"prt_d79501d9b001ibyZW0NFhvLOHa","messageID":"msg_d795013b90015NPREAw4fOe3mL","sessionID":"ses_286b0173effehMzZXYWbZMW44j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_079ccbe28ea94822b4306648","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement file management REST API for the PicoD service in `pkg/picod`, enabling upload, download, list, and deletion of files within sandbox workspaces. The API integrates with the existing Kubernetes client-go library for resource management.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The PicoD service (AR-015) runs as a sandbox execution environment requiring file management capabilities for code execution workflows. Current implementation includes basic file handlers but needs a structured REST API surface with proper error handling, path validation, and integration with the agentcube client-go library.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Implement a comprehensive file management REST API in `pkg/picod` with:\n16: - RESTful endpoints for file CRUD operations\n17: - Path sanitization and security validation\n18: - Support for multipart and JSON-base64 upload formats\n19: - Integration with client-go for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resource management\n20: \n21: ### Value\n22: - Complete file management capabilities for sandbox environments\n23: - Standardized REST API matching Kubernetes conventions\n24: - Path security to prevent directory traversal attacks\n25: - Support for both direct file upload and base64-encoded content\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Scope\n30: \n31: ### In-Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | File upload endpoint | POST /api/v1/files — multipart and JSON-base64 |\n36: | File download endpoint | GET /api/v1/files/*path |\n37: | File list endpoint | GET /api/v1/files?path=... |\n38: | File delete endpoint | DELETE /api/v1/files/*path |\n39: | Path sanitization | Validate and constrain paths to workspace directory |\n40: | Client-go integration | Resource read/write via informers/listers |\n41: \n42: ### API Endpoints\n43: \n44: | Method | Path | Description |\n45: |--------|------|-------------|\n46: | POST | /api/v1/files | Upload file (multipart or JSON-base64) |\n47: | GET | /api/v1/files | List files in directory |\n48: | GET | /api/v1/files/*path | Download file |\n49: | DELETE | /api/v1/files/*path | Delete file or directory |\n50: \n51: ### Data Types\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: type FileInfo struct {\n55:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n56:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n57:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n58:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n59: }\n60: \n61: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n62:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n63:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n64:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n65: }\n66: \n67: type FileEntry struct {\n68:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n69:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n70:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n71:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n72:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n73: }\n74: \n75: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n76:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n77: }\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Code Structure\n81: \n82: ```\n83: pkg/picod/\n84: ├── files.go           # File handlers (upload, download, list, delete)\n85: ├── server.go          # Server struct and initialization\n86: ├── config.go          # Configuration parsing\n87: ├── auth.go            # Authentication middleware\n88: ├── execute.go         # Code execution handlers\n89: ├── health.go          # Health check endpoints\n90: ├── picod_test.go      # Unit tests\n91: └── main.go            # Entry point\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### Configuration\n95: \n96: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n97: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n98: | PICOD_PORT | No | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n99: | PICOD_WORKSPACE_DIR | Yes | - | Base workspace directory |\n100: | PICOD_AUTH_TOKEN | No | - | Authentication token |\n101: | KUBERNETES_MODE | No | false | Enable Kubernetes client-go |\n102: | KUBERNETES_API_SERVER | No | in-cluster | API server URL |\n103: | KUBERNETES_CONFIG | No | in-cluster | kubeconfig path |\n104: \n105: ### Out-of-Scope\n106: - File streaming for large files (>100MB)\n107: - Directory creation endpoint (implicit via upload)\n108: - File move/rename operations\n109: - File content search\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## Impact Analysis\n114: \n115: ### Dependencies\n116: \n117: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n118: |------------|--------|---------|\n119: | github.com/gin-gonic/gin | ^1.x | HTTP framework |\n120: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client | local | Kubernetes client-go |\n121: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | CRD types |\n122: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging |\n123: | k8s.io/client-go | ^0.34.x | Kubernetes client |\n124: \n125: ### Upstream\n126: \n127: - **AR-015 PicoD Service** — Base service infrastructure\n128: - **client-go library** — Generated Kubernetes client (deployment/client-go.md)\n129: - **pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1** — AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\n130: \n131: ### Downstream Consumers\n132: \n133: 1. **Code Execution Workflows** — Source file upload, output retrieval\n134: 2. **IDE Integrations** — File sync capabilities\n135: 3. **Test Frameworks** — Test file deployment\n136: \n137: ### Risks\n138: \n139: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n140: |------|----------|------------|\n141: | Path traversal | High | SanitizePath with workspace root validation |\n142: | Large file DoS | Medium | Size limits on upload |\n143: | Path injection | Medium | Reject absolute paths and parent directory refs |\n144: | Concurrent writes | Low | OS-level file locking for overwrite detection |\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## Alternatives Considered\n149: \n150: ### Option 1: Direct Filesystem Access (Selected)\n151: \n152: **Approach**: Use Go's os/std library directly for file operations.\n153: \n154: **Pros**:\n155: - Simple implementation\n156: - No external dependencies\n157: - Direct control over file operations\n158: - Works in any environment\n159: \n160: **Cons**:\n161: - No distributed filesystem support\n162: - Local-only storage\n163: \n164: **Decision**: Selected — aligns with PicoD's isolated sandbox model.\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Option 2: Kubernetes PersistentVolume\n169: \n170: **Approach**: Mount PVC for workspace storage.\n171: \n172: **Pros**:\n173: - Persistent across pod restarts\n174: - Distributed access\n175: \n176: **Cons**:\n177: - Requires PVC provisioning\n178: - Overhead for ephemeral sandboxes\n179: - Complex lifecycle management\n180: \n181: **Decision**: Deferred — not needed for ephemeral execution model.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ### Option 3: Object Storage (S3/MinIO)\n186: \n187: **Approach**: Store files in object storage.\n188: \n189: **Pros**:\n190: - Scalable\n191: - Built-in redundancy\n192: \n193: **Cons**:\n194: - Network latency\n195: - Additional infrastructure\n196: - Not needed for execution artifacts\n197: \n198: **Decision**: Deferred — future consideration for multi-pod deployments.\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Implementation Plan\n203: \n204: ### Phase 1: Core Handlers\n205: - [x] UploadFileHandler — multipart and JSON-base64\n206: - [x] ListFilesHandler — directory listing\n207: - [x] DownloadFileHandler — file retrieval\n208: - [ ] DeleteFileHandler — file/directory removal\n209: - [x] Path sanitization with workspace root validation\n210: \n211: ### Phase 2: Client-go Integration\n212: - [ ] Initialize SharedInformerFactory\n213: - [ ] Wire AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter listers\n214: - [ ] Add resource watch handlers\n215: \n216: ### Phase 3: Error Handling\n217: - [ ] Consistent error response format\n218: - [ ] Status code standardization\n219: - [ ] Logging integration\n220: \n221: ### Phase 4: Testing\n222: - [ ] Unit tests for each handler\n223: - [ ] Path sanitization edge cases\n224: - [ ] Integration tests with client-go\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Acceptance Criteria\n229: \n230: - [x] POST /api/v1/files accepts multipart/form-data\n231: - [x] POST /api/v1/files accepts application/json with base64 content\n232: - [x] GET /api/v1/files lists directory contents\n233: - [x] GET /api/v1/files/*path downloads file\n234: - [x] DELETE /api/v1/files/*path removes file/directory\n235: - [x] Path traversal attacks prevented via SanitizePath\n236: - [x] Absolute paths rejected\n237: - [x] Parent directory references (..) rejected\n238: - [x] Files constrained to workspace directory\n239: - [x] File mode parsed from request (octal string)\n240: - [x] Default file mode 0644\n241: - [x] ListFilesResponse returns proper FileEntry array\n242: - [x] 404 returned for non-existent paths\n243: - [x] 400 returned for invalid requests\n244: - [ ] Client-go informer factory initialized\n245: - [ ] AgentRuntime lister integrated\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement file management REST API for the PicoD service in `pkg/picod`, enabling upload, download, list, and deletion of files within sandbox workspaces. The API integrates with the existing Kubernetes client-go library for resource management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe PicoD service (AR-015) runs as a sandbox execution environment requiring file management capabilities for code execution workflows. Current implementation includes basic file handlers but needs a structured REST API surface with proper error handling, path validation, and integration with the agentcube client-go library.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement a comprehensive file management REST API in `pkg/picod` with:\n- RESTful endpoints for file CRUD operations\n- Path sanitization and security validation\n- Support for multipart and JSON-base64 upload formats\n- Integration with client-go for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resource management\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775856787672,"end":1775856787689}}}}
